==English==

===Etymology===
[[French]]; '''''drôle''''' "buffoon" from [[Old French]] '''''drolle''''' (possibly from [[Middle Dutch]] '''''drol''''' "fat little man" or [[Middle High German]] '''''trolle''''' "clown")

===Adjective===
'''droll'''
# [[odd]]ly [[humorous]]; [[whimsical]]

====Translations====

* French : [[fantaisiste]]
* [[Ido]] : fantaziema

===Adverb===
'''drolly'''
# to act in an odd or humorous manner

===Noun===
'''droll'''
# (archaic) a buffoon
'''drollness'''
# the quality of being odd or comical

